              <tr><td colspan="3"><hr width="100%" size="1"></td></tr>
              <tr><td colspan="3"><b>Description</b><br>
Kerra Ridge is one of those places that is often overlooked due to its many flaws. The Kerran's themselves are for the most part only good for xp between 12-18th levels, after that only the odd "higher" level High Guard, Chieftan and Mitty will give you xp. Kerrans when injured will always follow the same path, across the zone, leap into the water, swim under the bridge and suicide for 32000 points. This is rather annoying. Loot wise, your looking at low end gems, silver earings, the odd gold, lots of silver and fresh fish for you practising cooks. What Kerra is ideal for is a training (pun intended) area for guilds and other large parties.  Later on, at around 25th, people will begin to realize in places like Guk, Cazic Thule and Sol A, that having 2 parties
is better than one. Unfortunately there IS a learning curve to how to do this of about 2 weeks. Learning in Guk or Sol A is flat out deadly.
<br><br>
Kerra however is a fantastic simulator BECAUSE of its bad properties. The cats are VERY closely nested together and are social. Females will cast druid damage and the odd heal, Males are pure melee. Learning how to co-ordinate 2 or even 3 parties in such a volatile enviornment is a fantastic learning experience. The trains in Kerra ranged on average from 4 to 40 cats if someone were mad enough to just run in and kick Mitty then run out. Fighting in the valley directly in from the zone is recomended. If you need anti caster practice (Lower Guk, Sol B) send your parties over to the Necro island.
<br><br>
The only real item of note in this place otherwise is the Golden Ring needed for the "Paw of Opalla" Quest, which Mitty will drop VERY infrequently. The current record I believe is held by a shaman friend on E'Ci who had to kill 98 Mitties at level 24 and earned enough xp off her (as a green con) to level through his last bubble.
<br>
<i>Submitted By: Flynx - aka Kelnya Madweasel of Bertoxx</i><br><br>
