<a href="mailto:m025580@nadn.navy.mil">Entioch</a> of the Mithaniel Marr server on Jan. 22, 2000 at 03:37pm said...<br>
You might want to try going to Eruds Crossing for the Kerra Beetles.  If you are looking for Kerra Fire Beetle Eyes, this is the place to be.  Be careful, though, as the Kerrans in the crossing are fond of their beetles and will join in the attack if they see you.<br><br>
<a href="mailto:GenM1A1@aol.com">Sinuuyanea</a> of the Quellious server on Jan. 20, 2000 at 06:08pm said...<br>
Are the Kerrans friendly to Dark Elves or Necros?  A quest from Neriak requires me to kill the beetles there, and as anyone who's played a Dark Elven Necromancer knows, friends are few, far between, and to be cherished (until they outlive their usefulness or start dropping good items...)<br><br>
<a href="mailto:mwyble@hotmail.com">Drumil</a> of the Fennin Rop server on Jan. 01, 2000 at 03:11pm said...<br>
The landscape is NOT ocean, it is a mix with land areas and a large lake both included.<br><br>
<a href="mailto:schattendrachen@hotmail.com">Schatten</a> of the The Rathe server on Nov. 09, 1999 at 12:13pm said...<br>
I totally disagree.  Although they DO need to fix some nasty design problems, like the kitties jumping in the river and drowning when they get weak, with a few tweaks, it could be a VERY nice low level zone.  Oh, and high-levels have quite a few dungeons they can go hunt in, low-levels have Crushbone (super-crowded), Befallen(deathtrap), BlackBurrow(Well Made), and Kerra Isle(No Worthwhile Items that can be camped by someone in the level range the zone is meant for).  Oh, and who said those armor quests are supposed to be easy?  =)

Not that I can say anything on that one, I still have to camp Cazic-Thule for armor...  =|<br><br>
<a href="mailto:Fireball@bnv-bamberg.de">Militades Sunfire</a> of the Solusek Ro server on Nov. 09, 1999 at 06:45am said...<br>
The Icon of the Pentinent is located on the small Necro Isle. This item is required for the new Cleric Armor Quest. Guess how hard it is to clear the Necro Isle with around 12 Necros with Pet on it, so close to each other that even Calm doesn't work. And, to make it even more harder Maugarim (the Necro you oughta kill) spawns only every about 7 hours and only if you kill the others 1st so he got his spawn point free. ACK<br><br>
